OL,4,Cwelfare cuts?
OL,6,FThe government's own estimates also
OL,7,Fproject that among the 250,000 people
OL,8,Fpushed into poverty as a result of the
OL,9,Fchanges will be 50,000 children.
OL,11,FThe Liberal Democrats say the cuts are
OL,12,Fa "double whammy" hitting disabled
OL,13,Fpeople who cannot work while cutting
OL,14,Fsupport for their carers.
OL,16,FAs a result of the changes, a further
OL,17,F150,000 people will not receive
OL,18,Fcarer's allowance or the carer element
OL,19,Fof universal credit, the impact
OL,20,Fassessment showed.
